<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFF8FFD3FF6BFC93FE73FC5C" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF8FFD3FF6BFC93FE73FC5C" blockId="34.[151,1127,885,1004]" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF8FFD3FF6BFC93FEB8FC3C" bold="true" box="[151,262,885,908]" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF8FFD3FEF0FC93FEEDFC3C" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1952" box="[268,339,885,908]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aidoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF8FFD3FEF0FC93FEEDFC3C" box="[268,339,885,908]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">Aidoia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus traditionally placed in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF8FFD3FC6FFC93FC44FC3C" authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[915,1018,885,908]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
. Since 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF8FFD3FBBAFC93FE97FC1C" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aidoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubilosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF8FFD3FBBAFC93FE97FC1C" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">Aidoia nubilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a strongly transverse head with small eyes situated in front of mouthparts and prolonged ultimate tarsomere with long tarsal claws similar to other 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF8FFD3FC54FC53FBDCFC7C" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[936,1122,949,972]" pageId="34" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
, I transfer it to the latter tribe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
